NAVBAR COMPONENT
├── State: isMobile (true on phones, false on desktop)
├── useScrollPosition() → tells us how far we've scrolled
├── useToggle() → controls if mobile menu is open/closed
├── useClickOutside() → closes menu when clicking outside
├── useActiveSection() → highlights current section in navbar
└── Render: Shows different layout for mobile vs desktop

HOW IT ALL WORKS TOGETHER:
1. When page loads → check if mobile or desktop
2. As user scrolls → navbar gets white background after 50px
3. On mobile → hamburger menu appears
4. Click hamburger → menu slides down
5. Click outside menu → menu closes automatically
6. Scroll to sections → nav links highlight automatically